news.title: Himachal Pradesh government yet to provide land for Gaggal airport expansion
news.para: The airports at Shimla and Kullu and the heliports at Rampur and Mandi in Himachal Pradesh have already been operationalised under the UDAN scheme, informed the Union minister.

news.title: Goa: High court seeks replies on illegal hill cutting in Calapur
news.para: The Goa State Expert Appraisal Committee, in the minutes of its 172nd meeting on March 10, 2023, recorded that the deponent was illegally undertaking mining of a hill under the pretext of requiring the soil for making a service road in Survey No. 110/1 and 111/1 at Calapur village.

news.title: Patna metro rail to become operational from August 15 next year: Deputy CM, Bihar
news.para: In the build-up to the assembly elections due next year, the new metro rail would be a shot in the arm for CM Nitish Kumar development agenda.

news.title: Can't install CCTV cameras in house without resident's consent: Calcutta HC
news.para: Calcutta High Court ruled that installing CCTV cameras in a co-owned residential property without the resident's permission is a violation of privacy. The court supported a woman's right to deactivate the cameras installed by her estranged husband in the Tollygunge property she primarily lived in, ensuring no disturbance occurred.

news.title: Nagpur property dealer arrested in Seoni for defrauding woman of Rs 42 lakh
news.para: According to the complaint filed by Gumgaonkar at Sakkardara police station, she had entered into an agreement with Paunikar for the purchase of a plot in Pimpaldhara, Hingna taluka.

news.title: Chennai civic body's commercial complexes remain vacant and struggle with low revenue
news.para: Despite being located in prime areas like T Nagar, Central, Anna Nagar, Ashok Nagar, and Alwarpet, these complexes struggle to attract customers, generating less than half of the ₹20 crore annual revenue target.

news.title: Bengaluru citizens form coalition to combat illegal construction
news.para: This initiative is in collaboration with several civil society organisations, including resident welfare associations, non-governmental organisations, Bangalore Apartments Federation (BAF), and active citizens.

news.title: Delhi LG approves reconstitution of construction workers welfare board
news.para: While giving his nod to its reconstitution, LG directed that immediate steps should be taken to implement Supreme Court directions to provide subsistence allowance to workers affected due to restrictions on construction activities because of high pollution levels in NCR states.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body halts construction of illegal apartment in Patia
news.para: According to sources, the real estate firm was allotted the land by the govt for industrial purposes, but instead, it started constructing a multi-storied residential apartment by illegally changing the type of plot to sthitiban.

news.title: Roorkee residents put ‘on sale’ notices on properties to protest waterlogging crisis
news.para: The road, which is around 60-foot-wide and connects around a dozen villages, has been plagued by waterlogging over a half-kilometre stretch for years due to the lack of a proper drainage system.

news.title: Goa government to enforce Rs 10,000 fine for unverified tenants from December 1
news.para: Residents of other states who moved to Goa were found to be involved in crimes in the state, from petty theft to a series of murders, prompting Chief Minister Pramod Sawant to direct the police to commence verification of those living on rent.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government identifies land bank for office space development in Chennai
news.para: It has identified 30 locations in Chennai for grade A office space development, said state industries secretary V Arun Roy.

news.title: Thirteen of 100 smart cities have completed all their projects: Centre
news.para: In a written reply to a question, Union Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Tokhan Sahu said more than 84,000 CCTV surveillance cameras have been installed and 713 kilometres of cycle tracks developed in 100 smart cities so far.

news.title: Housing ministry spends Rs 2.3 crore per month on consultants
news.para: The ministry spends around Rs 2.3 crore per month to pay salaries to these outsourced manpower, with some of them taking home between Rs 2.5 lakh to Rs 5 lakh, as per the details submitted by the ministry to Rajya Sabha.

news.title: Delhi LG approves redevelopment of slum areas under Jahan Jhuggi Wahin Makaan scheme
news.para: The modification in policy will allow projects to be more viable and more players could come forward for in-situ slum projects and thereby more houses could be built, officials said.

news.title: Consortium aims to take ESR Group private, valuing it at over $7 billion: Sources
news.para: Warburg Pincus, ESR's top shareholder with a 14% stake, plans to roll over its holdings into the future private company, rather than cash out, said the two sources and two other people with knowledge of the matter.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt launches hi-tech township near Jewar International Airport
news.para: The ambitious project by Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) is situated in Sector-24A of Noida, one kilometre from the International Film City, 500 metres from the Yamuna Expressway and close to the MotoGP track, an official statement issued here said.

news.title: High court stays clearance for 12-villa project at Paliem in Bardez
news.para: The petition challenges the technical clearance order granted for the construction in an orchard area with a no-development slope.

news.title: Investors can get co-developer status in GIFT SEZ commercial projects in Gujarat
news.para: ​​This opportunity emerged after the Union minister of commerce granted approval to an investor's application for co-developer status in GIFT SEZ's commercial tower Pragya, which houses the IFSC Authority headquarters and was developed by Savvy Group.

news.title: Haryana RERA mandates builders to submit annual reports within 30 days
news.para: The move comes after the regulator observed widespread non-compliance by promoters, raising concerns about transparency and accountability in the sector.
